From the sources
================
 * Install the dependencies ([[Requirements]]) don't forget the [eZ Components](http://ezcomponents.org/docs/install).
 * Download Gauffr.
 * Install the __Gauffr__ directory in __/usr/share/php__ or equivalent (Don't forget to check [set_include_path](http://php.net/manual/function.set-include-path.php)).
 * [[ConfigureGauffr]].
 * Use the install.php scripts:
~~~
cd Gauffr/scripts/
php install.php
~~~
 * Include Gauffr and [[UseGauffr]]

From RPM
========
 * Install the dependencies ([[Requirements]]) don't forget the [eZ Components](http://ezcomponents.org/docs/install).
 * Download and install the RPM of Gauffr and GauffrAdmin.
 * [[ConfigureGauffr]] in __/etc/gauffr/__.
 * Use the install.php scripts:
~~~
cd Gauffr/scripts/
php install.php
~~~
 * Include Gauffr and [[UseGauffr]].

With YUM
========
 * Use [my repository](http://www.llaumgui.com/pages/depot-llaumgui).
 * Install Gauffr on RHEL:
~~~
yum --enablerepo=remi,llaumgui,epel install gauffr gauffr-gauffradmin
~~~
 * Install Gauffr on Fedora:
~~~
yum --enablerepo=llaumgui install gauffr gauffr-gauffradmin
~~~
 * [[ConfigureGauffr]] in __/etc/gauffr/__.
 * Use the install.php scripts:
~~~
cd Gauffr/scripts/
php install.php
~~~
 * Include Gauffr and [[UseGauffr]].

